{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Impose financial penalties when parent is killed due to dangerous driving",
        "additional_details": "When a reckless driver takes a parent\u2019s life, the children left behind often lose both emotional and financial support. Current systems do not fully recognise the long-term impact on those children. Butler\u2019s Law would ensure courts can consider ordering the guilty party to pay financial support to the child. This way, responsibility would not end with a prison sentence.",
        "background": "We want courts to be able to order those convicted of killing a parent through drink driving, drug driving, dangerous driving or hit-and-run offences to pay ongoing financial support for the child. This could be known as \"Butler\u2019s Law\".",
